Written 2 Game

Matthias Fuchs

7/23/2019

Overall Effect

Writing evaluations impacts restrospective evaluations via two paths.

Writing impacts retrospective evalutions via increasing the clarity of ones own opinion and via increasing the interaction focus. While the indirect effect of opinion clarity is moderated by the valence of the consumption experience, the indirect effect of interaction focus always increases retrospective enjoyment.

Positive Condition

Prestudy gave this an enjoment rating of 4.78 / 7 (n=15).

Negative Condition

Prestudy gave this an enjoment rating of 1.5 / 7 (n=10).

The valley of confusion

Similarly, the same valley of confusion is observed. However, this time the increase in understanding caused by writing led to opinions becoming more negative in the negative condition.

The interaction of understanding and game valence

This increase in understanding then has a negative effect on th retrospective enjoyment

fit_enj=lm(enjoyment~understanding*gamegood+written+crm+I(crm^2),df)
plot_model(fit_enj, type = "int")+labs(x="Understanding (1-7)",y="Retrospective Enjoyment (1-7)")

The positive effect of writing on retrospective enjoyment (the interaction focus path)

Very similar to the effect of loyal consumers who complain like the service more (Umashankar & Dahl). Maybe it is that it isnt because the consumers are loyal, but because the consumers put more effort into complaining?

The effect of writing on retrospective enjoyment mediated by Duration and Liking.
